  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Developing Capacity on Sexual Violence</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Its specific objective is to: 

1.  train and sensitize community actors on gender equity, prevention and management 
of sexual and gender-based violence in the provinces of BURURI, MAKAMBA, RUTANA, RUYIGI, CANKUZO and 
KARUSI,
2.  to provide comprehensive care (psycho-social, medical and legal) of 100% of SV / GBV cases 
reported and referred to the health facilities of the provinces of BURURI, MAKAMBA, RUTANA, RUYIGI, 
CANKUZO and KARUSI.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The overall objective is to contribute to better prevention and management of sexual violence (GBV) and 
gender-based violence (GBV) in the BURURI, MAKAMBA, RUTANA, RUYIGI, CANKUZO and KARUSI Provinces.</narrative>
  </description>
